# Truvornex - Neighborhood Operating System
# AI Agent Configuration File

## PROJECT OVERVIEW
Truvornex is a production-grade neighborhood operating system serving four roles: customer, provider, admin, and committee member. It handles real money (PKR), bookings, identities, and community governance in a 25km-radius geographic context.

**Core Principle:** The platform is a living geographic snapshot. When a user opens Truvornex, the system instantly knows their exact location, zone, nearby provider counts, available services, and Simon recommendations based on real local supply and demand - everything is real, local, and live.

## TECHNICAL STACK

**Frontend:**
- React + Vite
- Tailwind CSS
- Lucide React icons
- shadcn/ui components
- Supabase client for some features

**Backend:**
- Node.js + Express
- PostgreSQL with PostGIS extension
- Simon multi-agent system with OpenRouter AI
- Session-based authentication

**Database:**
- PostgreSQL with PostGIS for geospatial queries
- GIST indexes on all geolocation columns
- Complex relational schema with users, providers, bookings, wallets

**AI/Intelligence:**
- Simon multi-agent system (8 specialized agents)
- OpenRouter API with model routing and fallbacks
- Server-Sent Events for real-time updates
- Persistent pattern learning with simon_memory table

