## DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW

**Making Changes:**
1. Read existing code to understand patterns
2. Follow existing conventions (naming, structure, style)
3. Test changes before committing
4. Update documentation if adding features

**Simon Agent Changes:**
- Update agent to accept locationContext parameter
- Include location in system prompts and user prompts
- Use geographic constraints in recommendations
- Update monitoring jobs for zone-specific tracking

**Location Features:**
- Always use PostGIS for distance calculations
- Implement proper GIST indexes for performance
- Handle location denial gracefully
- Provide fallbacks when location unavailable

**Frontend Location:**
- Use useGeolocation hook - never implement custom location logic
- Send location to server automatically via hook
- Show clear messaging when location is denied
- Display distance in km with 1 decimal place

## DEPLOYMENT NOTES

**Database Migration:**
- PostGIS extension must be available
- Run initLocationIntelligence() on startup
- Indexes created automatically
- Seed data for neighborhood zones

**Simon System:**
- Simon Monitor jobs start automatically
- Jobs run at configured intervals
- Simon actions logged for audit
- Memory cleanup runs every 24 hours

**Performance Considerations:**
- PostGIS queries depend on proper GIST indexes
- SSE preferred over polling for live data
- Simon AI calls have timeout and fallback logic
- Connection pooling for database efficiency

## IMPORTANT REMINDERS

**Never Do:**
- Never use text city matching as location substitute
- Never cache provider online status more than 60 seconds
- Never show providers as online if heartbeat > 8 minutes old
- Never compute distance in JavaScript - use PostGIS
- Never show counts including providers without recent heartbeats
- Never skip location detection on app open
- Never add comments unless asked
- Never use hardcoded API keys or secrets

**Always Do:**
- Always use PostGIS for geospatial queries
- Always require location for location-aware features
- Always provide clear messaging when location is denied
- Always use GIST indexes on geolocation columns
- Always implement proper error handling for location features
- Always follow existing code patterns and conventions
- Always test with real GPS coordinates when possible
- Always use the simon skill for InsForge backend tasks

